jobs.description:
As APAC Regional Privacy Officer, I was responsible for:
•	providing legal and compliance advice on all data privacy issues for 14 countries within the AsiaPac region.
•	embedding AZ's Global Data Privacy program regionally;
•	enabling business projects and objectives by providing SME advice on global IT system implementation with a focus on developing pragmatic solutions; 
•	conducting PIAs and cloud risk assessments of regional and global projects to advise on local data privacy risks in specific markets; 
•	supporting regional markets with drafting data privacy notices/consents; conducting supplier due diligence activities, including review of policies, advising on contracts, and negotiation of remediation actions; 

In September 2015, I was nominated to act as Global Chief Privacy Officer (maternity leave cover) for 11 months and, in addition to my regional role, was responsible for the continued strategic development and implementation of the global governance framework, which included:
• liaising with global senior leaders to ensure their understanding of AZ’s program, particularly during a period of significant organisational re-structure;  
• re-designing and simplifying core aspects of the existing program in response to operational changes and new strategic priorities;
• providing SME advice on complex emerging risks including the substantial increase in the use of data analytics and connected devices; 
• project management leadership of global projects impacting up to 100 markets; 
• developing a response plan to address the decision invalidating ‘Safe Harbor’ which included the establishment and chairing of a cross-functional working group to drive a global company-wide response; and
• leadership of a team of four located in Europe.  This included developing the strategic direction of the Global Privacy team’s business plan, including prioritisation of focus and resources.

•	Adviser to the Australian Privacy Commissioner on all international privacy and data protection issues, including:
-	Australia’s lead on the implementation of the APEC Privacy Framework, including advising on and project managing the negotiations of the APEC Cross-border Privacy Enforcement Arrangement (CPEA) which was endorsed by all 21 APEC Economies;
-	Liaising with the US FTC on the development of the Cross-Border Privacy Rules system;
-	Drafting Australia’s recommendations and input to the International Conference of Data Protection and Privacy Commissioners’ (ICDPPC) Resolution on International Standards of Privacy (the ‘Madrid Declaration’).
•	Providing regulatory guidance to Australian government departments, industry bodies and private sector entities regarding compliance and best practice approaches to privacy and personal information handling.
•	Extensive input into law reform including in the areas of Anti-Money Laundering/Counter-Terrorism Financing, international health and genetics, security, and privacy.

Responsible for developing and managing the High Potential Development Programs
      for the Group.  Involvement includes the nomination and candidate selection process,

      program development, management and assessment of the success of the program.

Jade has demonstrated experience managing, supervising and co-ordinating the workflow of a team of lawyers acting on a range of regulatory matters before the Independent Pricing and Regulatory Tribunal. She has experience managing matters in respect of the following regulated areas:
Local Government;
Water Licensing;
Energy Network Regulation (including electricity and gas licensing);
Public Transport; and
Special reviews referred to IPART by the Premier of NSW (for example, the review of rent models for social and affordable housing).

Resumed in the Sydney office of KWM in April 2017.


    Global Co-ordinator, King & Wood Mallesons Corporate, M&A and Securities Group,
      since 2013


    Previously:


    - Managing Partner, KWM EUME, 2016 - 2017;


    - Partner, Corporate, KWM London, 2015 - 2016;


    - Managing Partner,  M&A and Tax, KWM Australia, 2013 - 2014;



      - Chairman, King & Wood Mallesons Australian partnership, 2010 - 2012.

